_:N63ae9c363bcc42eb9033d58a8f366a08 <http://schema.org/description> "<p>Paul is accountable for Strategy and all aspects of Integrated Waste Management across Nuclear Waste Services. He originally joined the LLWR leadership team in 2021 from the Nuclear Decommissioning Authority.</p>\n\n<p>His background is in commercial leadership roles, including category management, procurement, and contract management within both highly regulated and public sector environments. He has a special interest in how public procurement can enable social value and support the delivery of benefit to local communities.</p>\n\n<p>Paul started his career as a Graduate Chemist in British Nuclear Fuels Ltd, and spent 15 years at Sellafield in a range of technical roles focussed on waste encapsulation and latterly commercial roles. He then spent time with Central Government, working for Crown Commercial Services and HMRC, prior to a return to the nuclear industry in 2020.</p>\n" .
